strings.Value: [Heal Rashor's wound] "You're bleeding. Let me help you."

{n}Exhausted from the battle, the lizardfolk breathes heavily as a shallow wound on his shoulder continues to bleed.{/n} "Warmblood save Rashor. Rashor owe warmblood his life. Have nothing to thank now. Come to village, Rashor thank properly."
"Near gleaming lake, where river flows... Rashor forget how warmbloods call it... Where swamps are. Easy find, yes."
"Longtail tribe not enemy to warmbloods. We speak your language, we trade. Sometimes we eat traveler or two, but with no hate."
"Thickskin tribe not like us. They hate warmbloods â€” not speak their language, raze their villages, yes! They say must eat all warmbloods and lizardfolk will rule the earth as in times of old."
"Thickskin say Longtail sold hearts to warmbloods, say that why we become sick and lose scales soon-soon. That why we fight."
{n}The lizardfolk hisses gratefully.{/n} "Let always be peace between our two tribes, yes!"
